1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:01:00,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:01:34,890 --> 00:01:37,710
[Bloom Life]

3
00:01:38,570 --> 00:01:41,680
[Year 2014]

4
00:01:41,910 --> 00:01:43,710
You ran pretty fast, didn't you?

5
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:47,280
Not bad-looking either.

6
00:01:47,410 --> 00:01:48,930
Where are you running off to?

7
00:01:48,930 --> 00:01:50,070
You're actually quite good-looking.

8
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:50,479
Run?

9
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:51,270
Where to?

10
00:01:51,270 --> 00:01:52,670
Where are you running to?

11
00:01:52,780 --> 00:01:53,840
What are you doing?

12
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:25,520
Director,

13
00:02:25,780 --> 00:02:26,370
I understand

14
00:02:26,370 --> 00:02:27,640
what happened now.

15
00:02:28,329 --> 00:02:29,170
As for Xia Zi,

16
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,380
I will take her back.

17
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:31,910
Mother of Xia Zi,

18
00:02:31,930 --> 00:02:34,250
Xia Zi may be doing well in school,

19
00:02:34,490 --> 00:02:36,170
but she also needs to follow the rules.

20
00:02:36,170 --> 00:02:37,130
Xia Zi!

21
00:02:41,030 --> 00:02:42,690
Do you know what you did wrong?

22
00:02:43,090 --> 00:02:45,530
Did you use the self-defense techniques
I taught you?

23
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:47,570
Did you use the
"three-move victory" technique too late?

24
00:02:47,570 --> 00:02:49,310
Don't you know how to read the situation?

25
00:02:49,310 --> 00:02:50,810
In the face of three punks,

26
00:02:50,810 --> 00:02:52,940
how could you three girls take them on?

27
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:54,510
If you can't beat them,

28
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,940
running away is the best strategy.

29
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:56,540
Director,

30
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:59,410
I will definitely discipline her well
when we get home.

31
00:02:59,410 --> 00:03:00,620
I'll be leaving now.

32
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:02,630
I still have to get back to work.

33
00:03:18,940 --> 00:03:19,840
Who are you?

34
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,180
What are you trying to do?

35
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:22,110
What do you want?

36
00:03:24,490 --> 00:03:25,640
Just you wait!

37
00:03:37,740 --> 00:03:41,420
[Episode 3: There's more than
just nightingales in the rose garden]

38
00:03:46,750 --> 00:03:49,180
Sadiq was a jerk when he was a kid.

39
00:03:51,310 --> 00:03:54,240
I didn't expect his family to
own such a big silk shop.

40
00:03:54,940 --> 00:03:56,070
Come closer to talk.

41
00:03:56,720 --> 00:03:57,740
Let me tell you.

42
00:03:57,740 --> 00:04:00,440
Their family has more than
just these businesses.

43
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:02,170
Do you see the woman in the back?

44
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,500
Gulhumar.

45
00:04:04,590 --> 00:04:05,940
She's truly somebody.

46
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:07,870
Everyone in the old town knows her.

47
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:11,560
So beautiful!

48
00:04:12,090 --> 00:04:13,180
How gorgeous!

49
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:16,370
My bride is so beautiful.

50
00:04:16,370 --> 00:04:17,399
You look good!

51
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:18,200
So beautiful!

52
00:04:20,060 --> 00:04:21,040
You look good.

53
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:24,400
Take a look.

54
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:32,159
Red still complements
the bride's complexion best.

55
00:04:32,159 --> 00:04:33,810
This red outfit is more festive.

56
00:04:33,810 --> 00:04:34,610
That's right.

57
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:36,480
But,

58
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,950
Mom, I've always wanted to wear white.

59
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:40,159
Exactly.

60
00:04:40,159 --> 00:04:42,600
Ever since she was a child, her dream
was to wear a white wedding dress.

61
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:43,770
Exactly, Auntie.

62
00:04:43,770 --> 00:04:45,570
White wedding dresses are
really trending right now.

63
00:04:45,570 --> 00:04:47,750
Minawar looks like a princess in white.

64
00:04:47,750 --> 00:04:49,100
It looks good on her.

65
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,370
Isn't it?

66
00:04:50,930 --> 00:04:52,310
She's so pretty,

67
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:55,060
and she's also the pillar of
our song and dance troupe.

68
00:04:55,060 --> 00:04:56,980
Everyone loves her.

69
00:04:56,980 --> 00:04:59,250
Not like our Qunduzay.

70
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:01,600
I asked her to come by and watch the shop,

71
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:02,950
but she couldn't be bothered.

72
00:05:02,950 --> 00:05:05,010
Mom, why are you talking about me?

73
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,560
But,

74
00:05:07,580 --> 00:05:10,440
if you are marrying into
a wealthy family like ours,

75
00:05:10,650 --> 00:05:13,560
you should wear
our shop's signature piece,

76
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:16,980
which is the red silk.

77
00:05:17,010 --> 00:05:18,920
A wedding should be red and prosperous.

78
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:20,720
It's so festive. How beautiful!

79
00:05:20,790 --> 00:05:21,800
What do you think?

80
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:23,620
I...

81
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,840
Red looks festive.

82
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,630
If you want it to be festive,

83
00:05:34,650 --> 00:05:36,230
then let us bridesmaids wear it.

84
00:05:36,230 --> 00:05:38,260
There are so many of us bridesmaids.

85
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,460
If everyone wears red,

86
00:05:39,460 --> 00:05:40,890
it will be even more festive.

87
00:05:40,890 --> 00:05:41,510
Looks good, no?

88
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:43,560
Auntie, your silk is really beautiful.

89
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,180
Exactly.

90
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:45,310
So red and prosperous.

91
00:05:45,310 --> 00:05:46,300
Exactly, Auntie.

92
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:47,830
There are 8 of us in the bridal party.

93
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:49,159
That's 8 of us wearing red.

94
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:49,920
Exactly.

95
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:50,870
Imagine everyone wearing red

96
00:05:50,870 --> 00:05:52,070
while holding up your white dress for you.

97
00:05:52,070 --> 00:05:53,900
Right, how beautiful that would be!

98
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:54,970
I want to wear it.

99
00:05:54,990 --> 00:05:56,280
I want to wear it too.

100
00:05:56,860 --> 00:05:57,830
Let us wear red.

101
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:59,230
Qunduzay can wear it too.

102
00:05:59,330 --> 00:06:00,300
I'll take a call.

103
00:06:00,480 --> 00:06:02,420
Auntie, this silk is so comfortable

104
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:03,040
and so soft to the touch.

105
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,170
What style do you think we should make?

106
00:06:06,740 --> 00:06:07,500
Thank you.

107
00:06:09,140 --> 00:06:10,450
Grandma.

108
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:13,480
The flowers of our family
are so beautiful!

109
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,180
So beautiful!

110
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:17,040
Just like flowers.

111
00:06:18,980 --> 00:06:19,980
Where is my dad?

112
00:06:20,410 --> 00:06:22,190
Your dad went out early in the morning.

113
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:23,570
I don't know where he went.

114
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:25,570
He's probably hiding somewhere crying.

115
00:06:25,570 --> 00:06:26,810
How pretty!

116
00:06:26,810 --> 00:06:28,440
All of you better come back early, okay?

117
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:29,260
Okay.

118
00:06:29,370 --> 00:06:30,870
Don't worry, Mom.

119
00:06:30,870 --> 00:06:31,950
Today is Minawar's

120
00:06:31,950 --> 00:06:33,480
final bachelorette party.

121
00:06:33,659 --> 00:06:34,540
Okay.

122
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:35,230
Let's go.

123
00:06:35,230 --> 00:06:36,060
Please be safe!

124
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:37,370
I promise to bring everyone back safely.

125
00:06:37,370 --> 00:06:38,190
Bye bye!

126
00:06:59,010 --> 00:07:00,100
It looks good.

127
00:07:00,810 --> 00:07:01,360
I've been well.

128
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,160
How about you?

129
00:07:02,190 --> 00:07:03,410
My friend, you're here.

130
00:07:03,410 --> 00:07:04,450
I ran into him this morning

131
00:07:04,450 --> 00:07:05,860
and asked if he wanted to come over today.

132
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:07,860
I didn't expect him to actually come.

133
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:09,560
We happened to be short of a photographer.

134
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:10,620
Thanks for your hard work.

135
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,350
My pleasure.

136
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:13,560
No problem.

137
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:14,240
Right?

138
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:14,690
Yes.

139
00:07:15,570 --> 00:07:16,360
Go have fun.

140
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,430
Why are you everywhere?

141
00:07:25,570 --> 00:07:26,800
What are you talking about?

142
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,130
I'm here to take photos.

143
00:07:28,330 --> 00:07:29,560
Take photos?

144
00:07:29,590 --> 00:07:31,180
I think you're just trying to
get on my good side.

145
00:07:31,180 --> 00:07:31,940
Don't you tell anyone

146
00:07:31,940 --> 00:07:32,820
about my work.

147
00:07:34,210 --> 00:07:35,670
You're being too cynical.

148
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,130
Don't worry.

149
00:07:37,130 --> 00:07:38,330
I'll keep it a secret.

150
00:07:39,370 --> 00:07:41,210
Hello, buddies!

151
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:43,180
You're dressed so nicely today.

152
00:07:43,180 --> 00:07:44,630
You're dressed well too.

153
00:07:46,620 --> 00:07:48,050
Bro!

154
00:07:48,570 --> 00:07:49,510
Long time no see.

155
00:07:51,310 --> 00:07:52,440
It's been a long time.

156
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,700
How did you get so buff?

157
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:54,450
Xia Zi.

158
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,690
So formal-looking!

159
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,180
Who is this friend?

160
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:01,000
-He's Arzugul's friend.
-He’s from our homestay.

161
00:08:01,490 --> 00:08:02,400
Let's take a photo.

162
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,060
Let's go.

163
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:04,880
Let's all take a photo together!

164
00:08:05,120 --> 00:08:05,980
Um,

165
00:08:05,980 --> 00:08:06,480
friend?

166
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:06,980
Could you do us a favor

167
00:08:06,980 --> 00:08:07,830
and take a picture of us?

168
00:08:07,830 --> 00:08:08,500
Thanks.

169
00:08:12,190 --> 00:08:12,770
Come.

170
00:08:12,990 --> 00:08:13,870
Look at me.

171
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,010
Get ready.

172
00:08:17,950 --> 00:08:18,890
Smile!

173
00:08:18,890 --> 00:08:20,060
3,

174
00:08:20,060 --> 00:08:21,100
2,

175
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:21,890
1.

176
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:24,150
Cheese!

177
00:08:25,260 --> 00:08:26,140
Hi.

178
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,040
Adili.

179
00:08:47,370 --> 00:08:47,920
No, no.

180
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,680
This is a wedding gift for you.

181
00:08:51,810 --> 00:08:53,610
We've known each other for so many years.

182
00:08:53,610 --> 00:08:54,570
Even if we're only friends,

183
00:08:54,570 --> 00:08:56,300
I should give you a decent gift.

184
00:08:57,660 --> 00:08:58,640
But...

185
00:08:59,240 --> 00:09:01,040
I wouldn't accept gold from any man

186
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:03,770
other than my husband and my father.

187
00:09:15,070 --> 00:09:16,020
6 months ago,

188
00:09:17,140 --> 00:09:18,380
before I went abroad,

189
00:09:19,380 --> 00:09:21,180
I asked you what gift you wanted.

190
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:22,660
You said you wanted someone

191
00:09:22,660 --> 00:09:24,590
who could give you a gold necklace.

192
00:09:25,260 --> 00:09:27,460
I thought you wanted me to give it to you.

193
00:09:30,950 --> 00:09:32,680
But when I came back,

194
00:09:33,330 --> 00:09:34,930
you already had a boyfriend.

195
00:09:36,970 --> 00:09:38,990
I've been wanting to ask you
for the past 6 months,

196
00:09:38,990 --> 00:09:39,810
why did you

197
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:44,610
change so quickly?

198
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:50,140
Actually,

199
00:09:51,080 --> 00:09:52,580
I have never changed.

200
00:09:53,230 --> 00:09:55,020
You've always known what I want.

201
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:56,570
I know you want to leave this place.

202
00:09:56,570 --> 00:09:57,710
I've been saving up money.

203
00:09:57,710 --> 00:09:59,710
But how much longer do I have to wait?

204
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:03,970
Adili.

205
00:10:04,660 --> 00:10:06,180
In a few years, I'll be old.

206
00:10:22,090 --> 00:10:24,640
Give this to the girl who’ll marry you.

207
00:10:47,300 --> 00:10:49,440
Thank you.

208
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,880
Blessed marriage!

209
00:10:49,670 --> 00:10:51,950
♪There's no intentional reason ♪

210
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,870
Thank you

211
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:54,380
♪I just love being proud and wild♪

212
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:55,150
Cheers

213
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:56,400
♪Until you leave me again♪

214
00:10:56,430 --> 00:10:58,890
♪I love freedom♪

215
00:11:00,810 --> 00:11:02,230
Come on, brothers.

216
00:11:03,670 --> 00:11:05,200
Come on, let’s have a drink!

217
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,720
Cheers.

218
00:11:12,950 --> 00:11:13,830
Come on.

219
00:11:15,810 --> 00:11:17,570
This is our local specialty,

220
00:11:17,660 --> 00:11:19,460
called "roasted sheep spleen".

221
00:11:19,540 --> 00:11:20,740
You don't dare to try?

222
00:11:27,230 --> 00:11:28,470
Isn't it delicious?

223
00:11:30,450 --> 00:11:31,230
Not bad.

224
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:38,850
Congratulations!

225
00:11:38,850 --> 00:11:39,730
You got prettier with age,

226
00:11:39,730 --> 00:11:40,760
and you're getting married now.

227
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:41,660
Don't just talk about me.

228
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:42,990
You should hurry up too.

229
00:11:43,140 --> 00:11:44,420
Look how formally he's dressed.

230
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:45,420
He must have heard

231
00:11:45,600 --> 00:11:47,160
your colleagues are all beauties.

232
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:48,470
Come on.

233
00:11:48,470 --> 00:11:50,330
Everyone knows he's here for you.

234
00:11:54,260 --> 00:11:55,040
Xia Zi.

235
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:58,040
Is your service really
this good these days?

236
00:11:58,040 --> 00:11:58,810
Why are outside guests

237
00:11:58,810 --> 00:12:00,440
allowed to join such private events?

238
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:02,490
He's here to help as a photographer.

239
00:12:05,710 --> 00:12:06,110
Right.

240
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:07,730
I suddenly remembered,

241
00:12:07,730 --> 00:12:09,190
previously,

242
00:12:09,190 --> 00:12:10,990
did Arzugul and Minawar both

243
00:12:10,990 --> 00:12:12,400
had a crush on Fang Nan?

244
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:13,900
Don't go saying things like that.

245
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:14,660
I didn't.

246
00:12:15,420 --> 00:12:16,020
No.

247
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:16,610
You didn't?

248
00:12:16,610 --> 00:12:17,310
No.

249
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:20,910
But it's not entirely accurate
to say not at all.

250
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:23,810
I might have liked him
for 2 or 3 months,

251
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,700
but I was just a kid then.

252
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:27,580
I was 2 heads shorter than I am now.

253
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:30,560
And in 6 months, you became just as tall

254
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:32,310
and as pretty as you are now.

255
00:12:32,420 --> 00:12:33,830
There were so many boys

256
00:12:33,830 --> 00:12:34,970
chasing after you.

257
00:12:34,970 --> 00:12:37,030
You must have forgotten him long ago.

258
00:12:37,180 --> 00:12:38,070
Exactly.

259
00:12:38,350 --> 00:12:40,210
But Arzugul is different.

260
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:42,660
She worked so hard to get into
a university in Shanghai.

261
00:12:42,660 --> 00:12:44,920
One summer, she even came all the way back

262
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,470
for some class reunion,

263
00:12:46,470 --> 00:12:47,850
just to see you once.

264
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:49,850
But you didn't even come.

265
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:50,630
Tell us,

266
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:51,660
where did you go?

267
00:12:54,180 --> 00:12:55,350
So,

268
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,600
that's how many things are.

269
00:12:59,660 --> 00:13:01,460
A series of unfortunate events.

270
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:08,780
When you need them,

271
00:13:09,140 --> 00:13:10,280
they aren't there.

272
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:13,390
What you want,

273
00:13:13,850 --> 00:13:15,210
they can't give.

274
00:13:19,310 --> 00:13:21,170
Even if you've tried really hard,

275
00:13:21,260 --> 00:13:22,060
but

276
00:13:23,060 --> 00:13:24,260
when there's no way,

277
00:13:25,400 --> 00:13:27,200
there's just nothing to be done.

278
00:13:28,830 --> 00:13:30,360
Don't you agree, my friend?

279
00:13:33,570 --> 00:13:37,730
♪My lover♪

280
00:13:37,730 --> 00:13:41,420
♪My flower-like lover♪

281
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:45,420
♪My dear lover♪

282
00:13:45,420 --> 00:13:49,420
♪Ah, oh, my dear♪

283
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:52,800
♪My beloved, whose eyes burn like flames♪

284
00:13:58,240 --> 00:14:00,000
Not bad!

285
00:14:01,350 --> 00:14:02,550
Come on, let's toast!

286
00:14:02,730 --> 00:14:04,030
Come on, cheers!

287
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:04,920
Let's have a toast too!

288
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:06,310
Come on, cheers!

289
00:14:06,310 --> 00:14:08,920
Cheers!

290
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:10,940
Come on, princess.

291
00:14:10,970 --> 00:14:12,020
Look,

292
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:14,340
a surprise for you.

293
00:14:16,770 --> 00:14:17,540
Let's go.

294
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:24,600
Beautiful, isn't it?

295
00:14:25,570 --> 00:14:26,570
Yes.

296
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:28,020
Sit.

297
00:14:28,350 --> 00:14:29,070
Sit down.

298
00:14:30,730 --> 00:14:32,230
Your Highness,

299
00:14:32,230 --> 00:14:33,350
have a grape.

300
00:14:33,380 --> 00:14:34,690
Let me

301
00:14:34,690 --> 00:14:36,140
massage your shoulders.

302
00:14:36,440 --> 00:14:38,070
Then let me

303
00:14:38,070 --> 00:14:39,540
massage your legs.

304
00:14:41,380 --> 00:14:42,900
You two maids

305
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,900
have served me very well today.

306
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:46,550
I will reward you

307
00:14:46,970 --> 00:14:48,490
by letting you sleep with me tonight.

308
00:14:48,490 --> 00:14:50,300
What?

309
00:14:50,300 --> 00:14:53,870
Shouldn’t you give us gold necklace?
Yeah.

310
00:14:53,890 --> 00:14:54,780
How dare you!

311
00:14:57,020 --> 00:14:58,040
You are the princess today.

312
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,430
Whatever you wish for tonight,

313
00:14:59,430 --> 00:15:00,660
we will satisfy you.

314
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,360
I want to dance the sanam.

315
00:15:03,600 --> 00:15:04,780
Go ahead, Your Highness.

316
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:05,680
Dance now.

317
00:15:19,730 --> 00:15:21,350
You can't do it. You're drunk.

318
00:15:21,350 --> 00:15:22,440
I can. Let's do it together.

319
00:15:22,440 --> 00:15:23,920
Come on, let's go.

320
00:15:24,330 --> 00:15:25,440
Let's go.

321
00:15:25,460 --> 00:15:27,060
Let's dance together. Come.

322
00:15:27,140 --> 00:15:27,880
Wait for me!

323
00:15:27,880 --> 00:15:30,180
My shoe broke!

324
00:15:52,470 --> 00:15:53,470
Minawar!

325
00:15:53,660 --> 00:15:55,880
Wishing you a happy marriage!

326
00:15:56,020 --> 00:15:57,180
Arzugul!

327
00:15:57,380 --> 00:15:59,280
Be forever free!

328
00:15:59,830 --> 00:16:00,680
Laili!

329
00:16:00,850 --> 00:16:02,560
Be happy everyday!

330
00:16:05,180 --> 00:16:06,980
I want to climb the Kunlun Tower.

331
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:09,140
Kunlun Tower is closed at night.

332
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:10,810
You can't go.

333
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:13,970
Then I want to see the golden sunrise
over the snow mountain.

334
00:16:13,970 --> 00:16:16,350
You're drunk. Don't go.

335
00:16:16,380 --> 00:16:17,860
No, I want to go!

336
00:16:17,880 --> 00:16:19,080
I'm getting married,

337
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:20,300
so I must go see it.

338
00:16:20,660 --> 00:16:23,690
You can't visit the snow-capped mountains
after you get married?

339
00:16:23,690 --> 00:16:25,850
I just want to see the sunrise.

340
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:30,010
Let's go see the golden sunrise
over the snow mountain, shall we?

341
00:16:50,490 --> 00:16:51,300
You're awake.

342
00:16:52,570 --> 00:16:53,810
Sleep a little longer.

343
00:16:53,810 --> 00:16:56,470
I'll wake you up when
the sun is about to come out.

344
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:00,200
How did I end up here?

345
00:17:03,570 --> 00:17:06,730
You were clamoring to see
the golden sunrise over the snow mountain,

346
00:17:06,730 --> 00:17:08,450
and wanted to dance at
the foot of the snow-capped mountains.

347
00:17:08,450 --> 00:17:09,450
I drank too much.

348
00:17:10,790 --> 00:17:12,440
You can't trust the words of a drunkard.

349
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,839
Take me back quickly now.

350
00:17:15,210 --> 00:17:16,030
Look outside.

351
00:17:35,270 --> 00:17:37,250
In the past, when I saw Muztagh Ata,

352
00:17:39,010 --> 00:17:39,750
it felt

353
00:17:40,230 --> 00:17:41,890
like it was so far away from us.

354
00:17:42,440 --> 00:17:43,510
But today,

355
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:46,360
it feels like it's right in front of me.

356
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:50,020
It's almost like I could touch it
if I just reach out.

357
00:17:53,190 --> 00:17:54,720
But, I still can't reach it.

358
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:56,770
Just looking at it is enough.

359
00:18:00,310 --> 00:18:01,640
Let's go back.

360
00:18:02,710 --> 00:18:03,910
Wait a little longer.

361
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:05,620
The sun is about to rise.

362
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:08,120
Minawar!

363
00:18:08,950 --> 00:18:09,750
Quick, look.

364
00:19:22,490 --> 00:19:23,440
Thank you

365
00:19:24,250 --> 00:19:25,090
for today.

366
00:19:26,820 --> 00:19:27,420
Minawar.

367
00:19:32,180 --> 00:19:33,710
I have one last thing to say.

368
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:37,180
In the past,
whenever you wanted to see me,

369
00:19:37,180 --> 00:19:39,380
I would do everything I could to show up.

370
00:19:40,290 --> 00:19:41,420
But not anymore.

371
00:19:46,380 --> 00:19:48,440
I wish to preserve some of my dignity.

372
00:19:51,860 --> 00:19:52,580
Goodbye.

373
00:20:24,510 --> 00:20:26,030
Your resume is excellent.

374
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:27,710
It was a pleasure talking to you today.

375
00:20:27,710 --> 00:20:29,640
Please wait for our notification.

376
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:31,220
I saw your job postings

377
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:32,860
and saw that
you're still hiring designers.

378
00:20:32,860 --> 00:20:34,680
I studied architectural design in college.

379
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,120
Can you give me a chance?

380
00:20:36,230 --> 00:20:37,950
I can start from the bottom.

381
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:40,160
Please just wait for further notice.

382
00:20:44,450 --> 00:20:47,060
Babes! Our itinerary today is to

383
00:20:47,090 --> 00:20:49,850
check out the top 10 homestays
in the old town.

384
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:50,490
Everyone will experience

385
00:20:50,490 --> 00:20:51,190
Our family's...

386
00:20:51,190 --> 00:20:53,970
the best of Kashgar’s charm!

387
00:20:53,970 --> 00:20:56,450
It's guaranteed to blow up
your social media feeds!

388
00:20:56,450 --> 00:20:58,190
Among these top 10
most beautiful homestays,

389
00:20:58,190 --> 00:20:59,790
some are famous for their food,

390
00:20:59,790 --> 00:21:03,450
some are decorated with the most complete
Southern Xinjiang handicrafts

391
00:21:03,450 --> 00:21:05,310
that boasts unique ethnic features.

392
00:21:05,310 --> 00:21:05,840
There is another one...

393
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:06,400
Uncle.

394
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,990
that would continuously
sing and dance for 15 hours.

395
00:21:08,990 --> 00:21:10,050
Has your homestay

396
00:21:10,110 --> 00:21:12,170
really been open for over a 100 years?

397
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:14,160
Young man.

398
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,230
didn't I show you the last time?

399
00:21:16,230 --> 00:21:18,290
The title deed written on sheepskin?

400
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:20,940
Have you ever thought about

401
00:21:20,940 --> 00:21:22,030
letting someone else

402
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:23,710
run this homestay?

403
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:27,120
Who would give their home up
to someone else?

404
00:21:27,120 --> 00:21:27,750
How dare you

405
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:29,370
boss around the house as an outsider?

406
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:30,860
I'm not dead yet, young man.

407
00:21:30,860 --> 00:21:31,810
Uncle,

408
00:21:31,900 --> 00:21:33,290
that's not what I meant.

409
00:21:33,870 --> 00:21:36,010
This is the first time I've seen a shop
with such a long history.

410
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:36,870
Standing here,

411
00:21:36,880 --> 00:21:38,600
it's as if I've traveled through
the corridor of time and space,

412
00:21:38,600 --> 00:21:40,390
and back to Kashgar 100 years ago.

413
00:21:40,390 --> 00:21:41,960
It's like I started...

414
00:21:43,920 --> 00:21:46,190
a dialogue through time and space.

415
00:21:48,010 --> 00:21:49,120
Young man,

416
00:21:49,530 --> 00:21:51,450
you have a great eye.

417
00:21:51,600 --> 00:21:52,400
Tell me,

418
00:21:52,790 --> 00:21:53,790
what's so good about

419
00:21:53,790 --> 00:21:55,250
this old homestay of ours?

420
00:21:58,230 --> 00:21:59,050
Uncle.

421
00:21:59,050 --> 00:22:00,290
When I was in Shanghai,

422
00:22:00,290 --> 00:22:01,290
I worked overtime every day,

423
00:22:01,290 --> 00:22:02,620
going home only in
the wee hours of the morning.

424
00:22:02,620 --> 00:22:04,160
And after going home,

425
00:22:04,180 --> 00:22:05,880
I was still too anxious to sleep.

426
00:22:05,880 --> 00:22:06,740
You have no idea

427
00:22:06,800 --> 00:22:08,180
how long it’s been since I’ve seen

428
00:22:08,180 --> 00:22:10,240
such beautiful sunshine in Kashgar.

429
00:22:10,320 --> 00:22:11,050
These 2 days,

430
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:12,710
I've slept very soundly,

431
00:22:12,710 --> 00:22:13,910
and very peacefully.

432
00:22:14,190 --> 00:22:15,820
I really appreciate it.

433
00:22:15,820 --> 00:22:16,160
I...

434
00:22:17,050 --> 00:22:19,380
I'm so, so grateful to you.

435
00:22:20,490 --> 00:22:21,320
Young man.

436
00:22:22,010 --> 00:22:23,880
It was fate that brought you

437
00:22:24,710 --> 00:22:27,100
to our homestay.

438
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,750
Old man, come up quickly!

439
00:22:28,940 --> 00:22:30,160
The faucet is leaking again!

440
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:30,990
Okay.

441
00:22:30,990 --> 00:22:32,120
I'll be right there!

442
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:33,290
Thank you, Uncle.

443
00:22:33,290 --> 00:22:33,820
I'll be right over!

444
00:22:33,820 --> 00:22:35,470
I'm on my way!

445
00:22:46,190 --> 00:22:48,650
Why are you trying to act like
such a hipster?

446
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:49,840
When you get off work
in the early morning,

447
00:22:49,840 --> 00:22:51,750
don't you get
your travel expenses reimbursed?

448
00:22:51,750 --> 00:22:53,810
Don't create a persona for yourself.

449
00:22:54,050 --> 00:22:54,710
I'm telling you,

450
00:22:54,710 --> 00:22:56,840
don't set your sights on our homestay.

451
00:23:01,080 --> 00:23:02,750
Don't tease our bird.

452
00:23:04,790 --> 00:23:06,050
Are we businesspeople

453
00:23:06,140 --> 00:23:07,990
not allowed to have sentiments anymore?

454
00:23:07,990 --> 00:23:10,720
Then you should go check out
the other homestays.

455
00:23:10,940 --> 00:23:11,820
To be honest,

456
00:23:12,340 --> 00:23:14,070
I've looked at many homestays.

457
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:15,990
Either

458
00:23:15,990 --> 00:23:17,720
I like them but lack the budget,

459
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:18,880
or I have the budget

460
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:20,680
but don't like them.

461
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:22,740
To put it bluntly, you're just broke.

462
00:23:24,190 --> 00:23:25,180
Does telling the truth

463
00:23:25,180 --> 00:23:26,190
do you any good?

464
00:23:27,010 --> 00:23:28,270
My friend,

465
00:23:28,270 --> 00:23:30,470
house hunting is a long game.

466
00:23:30,470 --> 00:23:32,290
Haste makes waste.

467
00:23:33,860 --> 00:23:35,860
The homestay market is saturated
in many areas

468
00:23:35,860 --> 00:23:37,790
but it's still growing in Kashgar.

469
00:23:38,070 --> 00:23:38,900
Opening a day earlier

470
00:23:38,900 --> 00:23:40,620
means making money a day earlier.

471
00:23:40,620 --> 00:23:42,620
You're really obsessed with money.

472
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:44,710
Who can compare with you?

473
00:23:44,710 --> 00:23:47,050
You have an apartment in Shanghai
to fall back on.

474
00:23:47,050 --> 00:23:48,450
Don't make fun of me.

475
00:23:49,140 --> 00:23:51,920
My uncle will see your true colors
sooner or later.

476
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,920
Worry about yourself first.

477
00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:56,470
You won't be able to hide the fact that

478
00:23:56,470 --> 00:23:58,070
you're unemployed for long.

479
00:24:12,270 --> 00:24:13,690
Hello, Aunt Jiang.

480
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:15,380
Xia Zi.

481
00:24:15,730 --> 00:24:16,860
I heard you're back.

482
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:18,640
Yes, I am.

483
00:24:19,230 --> 00:24:20,750
You probably don't know

484
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,950
about your mother's condition, do you?

485
00:24:23,340 --> 00:24:25,760
The famous traditional Chinese medicine
doctor, Director Chang,

486
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:27,870
is holding a clinic in the village today.

487
00:24:25,830 --> 00:24:27,750
[Chang Yue, TCM specialist at
Silk Road Hospital,  Kashgar Prefecture]

488
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:30,710
Please line up in an orderly manner.

489
00:24:31,180 --> 00:24:33,320
The famous traditional Chinese medicine
doctor, Director Chang,

490
00:24:33,320 --> 00:24:35,050
is holding a clinic in the village today.

491
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:37,860
Please line up in an orderly manner.

492
00:24:38,190 --> 00:24:39,320
Feeling any better?

493
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:41,470
My child had stomachaches for years,

494
00:24:41,470 --> 00:24:43,970
and you cured it with just 2 needles.

495
00:24:44,360 --> 00:24:46,600
Dr. Chang, you're amazing.

496
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:47,160
So amazing!

497
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:48,050
Mom—

498
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:49,400
My whole family is here.

499
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,290
Look, he's my dad.

500
00:24:51,290 --> 00:24:54,270
My mom, my brother, and his wife.

501
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,530
Hello.

502
00:24:55,530 --> 00:24:56,340
Thank you so much.

503
00:24:56,340 --> 00:24:57,790
You're welcome.

504
00:24:58,470 --> 00:24:59,400
Feeling better?

505
00:24:59,420 --> 00:25:00,360
Much better.

506
00:25:01,340 --> 00:25:03,140
It's time to remove the needles.

507
00:25:03,250 --> 00:25:04,120
Sir!

508
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:05,440
Sir!

509
00:25:08,270 --> 00:25:09,270
Oh, my medicine.

510
00:25:09,270 --> 00:25:10,790
Drink it.

511
00:25:14,510 --> 00:25:15,820
Well done.

512
00:25:16,090 --> 00:25:17,350
These elderly

513
00:25:17,380 --> 00:25:19,100
take the medicine home,
but don't take it regularly.

514
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:20,300
so the effect is poor.

515
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:21,420
After they take the medicine home,

516
00:25:21,420 --> 00:25:22,510
they quickly forget about it.

517
00:25:22,510 --> 00:25:24,840
They only come for medicine when
milk and naan are distributed.

518
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:27,280
They would give the milk and naan
to their children.

519
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,760
So you must watch them finish it.

520
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:29,690
Okay, Dr. Chang.

521
00:25:33,100 --> 00:25:34,730
You don't mind the fatigue either.

522
00:25:34,730 --> 00:25:36,900
Instead of seeing patients
in the hospital,

523
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:38,700
you came all this way to see them.

524
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:42,880
If I don't come down,
how can they understand

525
00:25:42,880 --> 00:25:45,280
and accept traditional Chinese medicine?

526
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:46,510
I tell them,

527
00:25:46,510 --> 00:25:47,790
you may focus on
dry versus damp heat,

528
00:25:47,790 --> 00:25:49,620
but we focus on damp heat
and qi stagnation.

529
00:25:49,620 --> 00:25:50,950
They are all connected,

530
00:25:51,010 --> 00:25:52,420
just different paths
to the same destination.

531
00:25:52,420 --> 00:25:52,820
Right?

532
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:53,510
Yes.

533
00:25:53,790 --> 00:25:55,270
You make a good point,

534
00:25:55,270 --> 00:25:56,670
but can your body take it?

535
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:58,120
I know my own body.

536
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,860
What do you know?

537
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:01,970
Aunt Jiang told me that

538
00:26:02,510 --> 00:26:04,650
your heart skips a beat tens
of thousands times a day.

539
00:26:04,650 --> 00:26:06,380
She suggests you have surgery.

540
00:26:07,510 --> 00:26:08,140
I'm fine.

541
00:26:08,820 --> 00:26:10,350
I'll take care of it myself.

542
00:26:10,550 --> 00:26:12,010
I just need some medicine.

543
00:26:12,450 --> 00:26:13,850
It's an emotional issue.

544
00:26:14,620 --> 00:26:17,100
Your dad has been gone
for more than half a year,

545
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:18,230
and no matter how much
I come to terms with it,

546
00:26:18,230 --> 00:26:18,910
well...

547
00:26:18,930 --> 00:26:19,690
I will still

548
00:26:19,970 --> 00:26:21,010
feel a little sad.

549
00:26:21,630 --> 00:26:22,980
I'm really at my wit's end with you.

550
00:26:22,980 --> 00:26:25,440
Why are you always
pushing yourself so hard?

551
00:26:29,210 --> 00:26:31,340
Why haven't you returned to Shanghai?

552
00:26:32,450 --> 00:26:33,360
Are you kicking me out?

553
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:34,880
I'll go back when I'm done.

554
00:26:37,490 --> 00:26:40,420
Are you not leaving
because you're worried about me?

555
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:45,680
Let me warn you.

556
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:49,290
I’ve raised you to be so outstanding,

557
00:26:49,710 --> 00:26:51,510
with the hopes that
as compared to our generation,

558
00:26:51,510 --> 00:26:53,770
you can make choices without any burden.

559
00:26:53,800 --> 00:26:56,600
I don't want you to
sacrifice yourself for anyone,

560
00:26:56,730 --> 00:26:58,340
nor will I allow anyone to bully you,

561
00:26:58,340 --> 00:26:59,400
including myself.

562
00:26:59,820 --> 00:27:01,140
So if you need to go back to Shanghai,

563
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:02,740
please go back immediately.

564
00:27:03,070 --> 00:27:05,530
I'll go back right after
Minawar's wedding.

565
00:27:09,020 --> 00:27:10,820
You'll go to her wedding, right?

566
00:27:11,110 --> 00:27:13,840
I'll see.
We've been really busy at the hospital.

567
00:27:21,100 --> 00:27:21,940
Old man,

568
00:27:22,250 --> 00:27:22,970
this was actually

569
00:27:22,970 --> 00:27:24,900
the rug we used when we got married.

570
00:27:24,950 --> 00:27:27,950
Yes, it's been almost thirty years
in a blink of an eye.

571
00:28:01,030 --> 00:28:02,700
Mom, you're not asleep yet?

572
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:06,680
My precious daughter
is getting married tomorrow.

573
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:09,640
How can any mother sleep?

574
00:28:18,790 --> 00:28:20,790
I bought this for you

575
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:22,730
when you were just born.

576
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:27,090
I bought this for you
when you went to primary school.

577
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:28,730
And this one

578
00:28:28,730 --> 00:28:30,790
was for when you got into high school.

579
00:28:32,580 --> 00:28:33,530
I got this one

580
00:28:33,860 --> 00:28:35,710
when you started working.

581
00:28:35,710 --> 00:28:36,970
Why did you buy so much?

582
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,080
Here, for you.

583
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:45,650
My secret stash that
I have been saving up for you.

584
00:28:47,790 --> 00:28:48,900
Thank you, Mom.

585
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:51,210
Thank you, Mom.

586
00:28:56,940 --> 00:28:58,380
Don't cry, silly child.

587
00:28:58,460 --> 00:28:59,940
Don't cry.

588
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:03,770
What mother doesn't start saving a dowry

589
00:29:03,860 --> 00:29:05,590
as soon as her daughter is born?

590
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,160
Mom.

591
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,170
You don't have to worry.

592
00:29:10,190 --> 00:29:13,190
Sadiq's business has reached Europe.

593
00:29:14,120 --> 00:29:15,160
You always knew

594
00:29:15,550 --> 00:29:16,510
that my biggest dream

595
00:29:16,510 --> 00:29:18,840
was to dance on a bigger stage.

596
00:29:19,490 --> 00:29:22,090
He’ll definitely help me
go to Europe to dance.

597
00:29:23,490 --> 00:29:25,470
You will go far

598
00:29:27,080 --> 00:29:29,080
and live the life you want.

599
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:32,400
Mom is happy for you.

600
00:29:34,180 --> 00:29:36,080
Don't cry. Don't cry.

601
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:39,440
Back then,

602
00:29:41,660 --> 00:29:43,080
I also wanted to

603
00:29:43,080 --> 00:29:44,880
go to Beijing to learn to dance.

604
00:29:48,840 --> 00:29:49,620
Later,

605
00:29:51,400 --> 00:29:52,750
I met your father

606
00:29:54,680 --> 00:29:55,680
and had you,

607
00:29:57,010 --> 00:29:58,920
so I stayed at this homestay.

608
00:30:01,790 --> 00:30:02,850
In a blink of an eye,

609
00:30:04,190 --> 00:30:06,320
most of my life has passed.

610
00:30:14,470 --> 00:30:15,470
Promise me

611
00:30:17,270 --> 00:30:18,490
you must live

612
00:30:18,920 --> 00:30:20,120
better than I did.

613
00:30:20,870 --> 00:30:22,500
I will. I promise you, Mom.

614
00:30:22,530 --> 00:30:24,680
Don't worry. I will.

615
00:30:25,280 --> 00:30:26,340
I definitely will.

616
00:30:28,470 --> 00:30:29,510
I promise.

617
00:30:53,790 --> 00:31:02,050
♪Congratulations♪

618
00:30:57,080 --> 00:30:58,120
They're coming!

619
00:31:04,150 --> 00:31:07,730
♪Celebrating a wedding with joyful steps♪

620
00:31:07,760 --> 00:31:10,460
♪May this couple’s hearts
always resonate together♪

621
00:31:18,340 --> 00:31:19,940
Brother, what are you doing?

622
00:31:20,050 --> 00:31:21,050
We have to leave soon.

623
00:31:21,050 --> 00:31:22,510
The car is parked outside.

624
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,650
Let's sit a little longer. No rush.

625
00:31:24,650 --> 00:31:26,070
Come, have some dessert.

626
00:31:26,800 --> 00:31:27,730
What's going on?

627
00:31:30,050 --> 00:31:30,940
The bride and groom

628
00:31:30,940 --> 00:31:32,660
still need to serve tea to their parents.

629
00:31:32,660 --> 00:31:34,320
Where did that rule come from?

630
00:31:36,180 --> 00:31:37,640
It's okay.

631
00:31:40,180 --> 00:31:41,530
What is this?

632
00:31:41,880 --> 00:31:43,010
How dirty!

633
00:31:51,310 --> 00:31:52,140
The car is loaded.

634
00:31:52,140 --> 00:31:53,070
We can leave now.

635
00:31:53,750 --> 00:31:54,950
You guys get in first. I'll wait a bit.

636
00:31:54,950 --> 00:31:55,530
Okay.

637
00:31:55,530 --> 00:31:56,260
Come, get in.

638
00:32:44,550 --> 00:32:45,640
Let's go!

639
00:32:58,760 --> 00:33:00,640
♪Along the way to Atushi♪

640
00:33:00,740 --> 00:33:03,140
♪The garden of Boshkeranmu is filled with
the sweet fragrance of flowers♪

641
00:33:03,580 --> 00:33:05,900
♪ I can smell the fragrance of
the Boshkeranmu flowers ♪

642
00:33:06,070 --> 00:33:08,470
♪The pain of a burning passion♪

643
00:33:08,590 --> 00:33:13,400
♪It's so torturing♪

644
00:33:13,430 --> 00:33:16,030
♪Gülayayim♪

645
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:18,780
♪My pain, Gülayayim♪

646
00:33:18,810 --> 00:33:21,020
♪What should I do, my lover?♪

647
00:33:21,610 --> 00:33:23,460
♪My pain, Gülayayim♪

648
00:33:23,610 --> 00:33:26,000
♪My heart burns for you always♪

649
00:33:27,290 --> 00:33:30,620
♪My heart burns for you always♪

650
00:33:31,150 --> 00:33:36,040
♪I belong to you, my lover♪

651
00:33:34,880 --> 00:33:36,180
What are they doing?

652
00:33:36,080 --> 00:33:38,500
♪Who else will I belong to, if not you?♪

653
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:37,440
In Xinjiang, people who can't dance

654
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:38,900
dare not attend weddings.

655
00:33:38,950 --> 00:33:41,470
♪You are the one I met
at the bazaar in Kashgar♪

656
00:33:39,230 --> 00:33:41,970
They are sending blessings
and red envelopes to the groom.

657
00:33:41,500 --> 00:33:43,220
♪You are whom I
fell in love  at first sight♪

658
00:33:43,820 --> 00:33:50,970
♪Hey, you are whom I
fell in love at first sight♪

659
00:34:01,730 --> 00:34:11,600
♪I came to your alley from my alley♪

660
00:34:04,230 --> 00:34:05,430
This is from your dad.

661
00:34:14,239 --> 00:34:16,440
This is the key to my house's front door.

662
00:34:51,989 --> 00:34:54,409
My granddaughter, you must be happy.

663
00:34:54,750 --> 00:34:57,790
You will always be Grandma's good girl.

664
00:35:12,260 --> 00:35:16,350
♪The snowflakes are falling♪

665
00:35:16,570 --> 00:35:21,100
♪In this last December♪

666
00:35:21,300 --> 00:35:25,940
♪The wind plays with the snowflake ♪

667
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:31,190
♪On either side of the streetlight♪

668
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:36,130
♪The snowflakes are falling♪

669
00:35:36,210 --> 00:35:41,130
♪In this last December♪

670
00:35:41,350 --> 00:35:45,380
♪The wind plays with the snowflake ♪

671
00:35:49,410 --> 00:35:51,930
Congratulations!

672
00:36:54,170 --> 00:36:55,320
What is this?

673
00:36:55,590 --> 00:36:56,720
They're competing.

674
00:36:57,240 --> 00:36:58,900
The groom's side will look for a chance

675
00:36:58,900 --> 00:37:00,780
to get under the red veil

676
00:37:00,940 --> 00:37:02,520
and lift the bride's veil.

677
00:37:02,540 --> 00:37:03,760
The bride's family must find a way

678
00:37:03,760 --> 00:37:05,500
to keep them out with the veil.

679
00:37:05,520 --> 00:37:06,640
If the veil is lifted,

680
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:08,370
it means the bride is captured.

681
00:37:38,740 --> 00:37:40,150
How could she do this?

682
00:37:40,150 --> 00:37:41,440
She just grabbed it?

683
00:37:41,440 --> 00:37:42,440
Does she know the rules?

684
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:43,970
The veil is torn.

685
00:37:56,930 --> 00:37:57,480
So,

686
00:37:57,550 --> 00:37:59,530
the groom's side has won?

687
00:37:59,550 --> 00:38:00,300
Yes.

688
00:38:00,300 --> 00:38:02,160
It's just a game that adults play.

689
00:38:12,300 --> 00:38:13,660
It's fine.

690
00:38:20,900 --> 00:38:23,090
Sadiq's family is going too far.

691
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:26,810
I'm really worried about her
marrying into that family.

692
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:44,970
Why did you come in this outfit?

693
00:38:45,640 --> 00:38:48,720
I just finished a home visit.
It's good enough I could make it.

694
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:50,050
What a busy bee.

695
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:53,330
Arzugul.

696
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:57,210
What's the name of the apartment
you bought in Shanghai?

697
00:38:57,650 --> 00:38:59,190
Rose Garden. What's wrong?

698
00:39:00,700 --> 00:39:03,230
The construction has been
halted for so long!

699
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:04,300
Give it to me. Let me take a look.

700
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:06,240
-Let me see.
-What's there to see?

701
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:09,040
Will construction at
Rose Garden ever resume?

702
00:39:09,340 --> 00:39:11,740
It's fine. It's just halted.

703
00:39:12,150 --> 00:39:14,180
So, are you still paying the mortgage?

704
00:39:14,180 --> 00:39:16,010
Yes. What else can I do?

705
00:39:20,860 --> 00:39:21,550
This is such a serious matter.

706
00:39:21,550 --> 00:39:23,750
How long do you plan to
keep this from me?

707
00:39:24,970 --> 00:39:25,670
Arzugul,

708
00:39:25,940 --> 00:39:27,360
you put all your savings

709
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,760
into this house.

710
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:30,740
Will they stop building it?

711
00:39:32,360 --> 00:39:32,900
Fine.

712
00:39:33,930 --> 00:39:34,950
We're going to Shanghai tomorrow.

713
00:39:34,950 --> 00:39:35,880
I'll go with you.

714
00:39:36,780 --> 00:39:37,980
What are we going for?

715
00:39:37,990 --> 00:39:38,950
We homeowners are currently

716
00:39:38,950 --> 00:39:41,010
in negotiations with the developer.

717
00:39:41,070 --> 00:39:41,760
Stay out of it.

718
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:42,590
I can handle it myself.

719
00:39:42,590 --> 00:39:44,190
What experience do you have?

720
00:39:44,980 --> 00:39:45,980
I must go with you.

721
00:39:46,130 --> 00:39:47,360
And what will you do?

722
00:39:47,360 --> 00:39:48,580
You'll just cause more trouble.

723
00:39:48,580 --> 00:39:49,980
How will I cause trouble?

724
00:39:51,110 --> 00:39:52,320
Arzugul,

725
00:39:52,400 --> 00:39:53,430
if your mother goes with you,

726
00:39:53,430 --> 00:39:58,120
she can at least cook for you
and help you out.

727
00:39:58,140 --> 00:39:59,080
This is such a big deal.

728
00:39:59,080 --> 00:40:00,310
It's not just your mom—

729
00:40:00,310 --> 00:40:01,690
we're worried too.

730
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:03,450
Exactly.

731
00:40:03,490 --> 00:40:04,400
This is so annoying.

732
00:40:04,400 --> 00:40:05,900
Laili, help me buy a flight ticket.

733
00:40:05,900 --> 00:40:07,190
I said no.

734
00:40:07,230 --> 00:40:08,090
Buy me a flight ticket.

735
00:40:08,090 --> 00:40:08,650
No, we are not going.

736
00:40:08,650 --> 00:40:09,330
This is such a big deal

737
00:40:09,330 --> 00:40:10,630
and you didn't even tell me.

738
00:40:10,630 --> 00:40:12,360
I'm not going back to Shanghai!

739
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:20,690
I lost my job.

740
00:40:21,090 --> 00:40:22,090
I was laid off.

741
00:40:22,780 --> 00:40:24,440
I just found out a few days ago.

742
00:40:27,310 --> 00:40:28,190
It's fine.

743
00:40:29,970 --> 00:40:31,470
Calm down, both of you.

744
00:40:31,490 --> 00:40:33,020
Arzugul is so outstanding.

745
00:40:33,160 --> 00:40:36,020
I'm sure plenty of companies
have reached out to her.

746
00:40:36,020 --> 00:40:37,400
Yue, don't you think so?

747
00:40:37,780 --> 00:40:38,450
Yes.

748
00:40:38,470 --> 00:40:39,270
You're right.

749
00:40:45,270 --> 00:40:46,710
Arzugul!

750
00:40:53,510 --> 00:40:54,490
Arzugul!

751
00:40:55,610 --> 00:40:56,300
Xia Zi.

752
00:40:59,150 --> 00:41:00,750
What's wrong with you today?

753
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:02,240
With so many people around,

754
00:41:02,240 --> 00:41:03,010
what do you mean

755
00:41:03,010 --> 00:41:03,550
by leaving so suddenly?

756
00:41:03,550 --> 00:41:03,840
No.

757
00:41:03,860 --> 00:41:04,380
Minawar.

758
00:41:04,380 --> 00:41:05,580
She didn't mean that.

759
00:41:05,710 --> 00:41:07,170
She has her own issues.

760
00:41:07,380 --> 00:41:08,700
Don't talk about me.

761
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,670
I don't understand.

762
00:41:09,670 --> 00:41:11,170
You're such a headstrong person.

763
00:41:11,170 --> 00:41:12,970
Today, from you to Uncle to Auntie,

764
00:41:12,970 --> 00:41:14,620
everyone seemed to be
bowing down to their family.

765
00:41:14,620 --> 00:41:15,650
Was it really necessary?

766
00:41:15,650 --> 00:41:16,960
Don't talk about this today.

767
00:41:16,960 --> 00:41:18,730
I'm just upset for her.

768
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:19,910
I feel bad for her.

769
00:41:20,660 --> 00:41:21,820
Who are they to do so?

770
00:41:22,110 --> 00:41:23,840
What gives them the right
to treat her this way?

771
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:24,590
It's her wedding.

772
00:41:24,590 --> 00:41:25,760
Why should they?

773
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:29,200
Aunt Chang Yue.

774
00:41:30,700 --> 00:41:31,590
What's wrong?

775
00:41:32,450 --> 00:41:33,380
Aunt Chang Yue.

776
00:41:36,110 --> 00:41:38,310
Minawar is so beautiful today.

777
00:41:40,620 --> 00:41:43,890
You and Sadiq really are enemies
who were destined to meet.

778
00:41:45,110 --> 00:41:46,600
I remember when you were

779
00:41:46,720 --> 00:41:48,450
around 14 or 15,

780
00:41:48,790 --> 00:41:51,060
Sadiq and two punks

781
00:41:51,510 --> 00:41:52,910
got into a fight with you.

782
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:55,440
It went all the way up to
the Office of Academic Affairs.

783
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:58,100
I was the one who
taught him a lesson afterwards.

784
00:41:59,070 --> 00:42:00,200
It was you?

785
00:42:01,080 --> 00:42:02,810
Why do I remember it being Dad?

786
00:42:02,990 --> 00:42:03,990
How could it be your dad?

787
00:42:03,990 --> 00:42:06,850
Your dad was working on
a mission abroad at the time.

788
00:42:20,310 --> 00:42:21,400
Just you wait!

789
00:42:33,410 --> 00:42:34,740
So it was Aunt Chang Yue.

790
00:42:35,360 --> 00:42:36,320
That's so cool.

791
00:42:41,560 --> 00:42:43,020
I'm not going to Shanghai.

792
00:42:43,440 --> 00:42:45,060
The moon waxes and wanes,

793
00:42:45,430 --> 00:42:47,450
and bad things happen,

794
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:49,150
but they will pass.

795
00:42:50,650 --> 00:42:51,980
But Mom believes in you.

796
00:42:52,590 --> 00:42:54,190
I've raised you to be someone

797
00:42:55,220 --> 00:42:56,510
who's not easily bullied.
